modules.description: Handles parameter definitions in recipes, providing access to parameter names, descriptions, and default values. Works with the `Bap_recipe.param` type to extract and display parameter metadata. Useful for inspecting or printing configuration options of a recipe without modifying their values.

This module loads and processes recipe files, providing access to their commands, arguments, and parameters. It works with strings, arrays, and custom types for recipes and errors. Use it to execute or inspect BAP recipes programmatically.
